# gen211 (cardinal KB-first principle): the surface forms that mean "ask my name" are
# KB knowledge (intent_phrase/2 in kb/core/intents.p0), matched by kb_intent_match, and
# the class GROWS at runtime. Here parrot0 is taught a brand-new form interactively and
# the very next turn it recalls the name through it — no code edit, no new handler. This
# is gen193's "the engine is fixed; the lexicon learns" lifted from words to multi-word
# idioms. (Persistence across sessions via /save is covered by the C path; this case
# ratchets the in-session dynamism hermetically.)
> my name is Ada
< Nice to meet you, Ada!
> learn "how do you call me" as asking my name
< Got it - I'll take "how do you call me" as a way to ask your name now.
> how do you call me
< Your name is Ada.
